MOBSection.Text1: Face masks required for all travelers
MOBSection.Text2: Federal law requires all travelers to wear a face mask with no vents or openings that fully covers their nose and mouth. Masks must be worn in the airport and during the entire flight, and between bites and sips if travelers are eating or drinking. Travelers who aren't wearing their masks in the airport or on board may be refused transport, be subject to fines, and could also lose their travel privileges on future United flights. Children younger than 2 years old are exempt. Learn more

ReservationAgeBoundInfo.ErrorMessage: Children under the age of 5 cannot travel unless they’re accompanied by a parent, legal guardian or someone who is at least 18 years old.
